{
  "stem": "19969.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 187.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the meantime, I was commanding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our regimental commander, Colonel O'Brien, had come up and-- as well as General Frederick, who was the division commander.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a major general, Colonel O'Brien was a full colonel, I was a lieutenant colonel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were taking inventory and my company commander actually went inside of the stockade, part of-- there were some large buildings right inside the gate that was used as a-- that's where they prepared the food for the inmates, what little they got, which was very little.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were all-- practically all of them were terribly emaciated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had two barracks in there that were filled with sort of an infirmary, two infirmaries.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And almost all the people in there were dying or some were already dead.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And some of them had been dead for several days, the ones lying out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that the smell of death was just overpowering.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were-- we were still having a difficult time [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] trying to comprehend.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We just couldn't-- it was hard to realize how those people have been treated-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we were still partly dazed, I'll say, at the-- the enormity of death there and the cruelty that went on there.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it did quieten down and C Company came up and took over the guarding of the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I then stayed there until about right at dark and saw that everything was fairly secure.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In the meantime, my battalion headquarters had moved up to the city of Dachau and established a headquarters there in a building in-- in the city.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one of the men from headquarters came up and took me back to the headquarters.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I didn't know where it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
